description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to start a new and exciting career within the NHS?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you enthusiastic, motivated with a desire to learn new skills? We are offering a new and exciting opportunity to join our Recruitment team as a Administration Apprentice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an apprentice you will gain valuable hands-on experience, whilst learning, and will work towards completing a Level 2 Business Administration Apprenticeship Certificate. Upon completion of your Level 2 apprenticeship you will achieve a nationally recognised qualification and the knowledge, skills and experience for a career in administration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual who has good interpersonal skills and is able to work well as part of a team. You will need to feel confident in communicating with others, as well as users of the service and their families and carers. You will be expected to be kind and responsive and contribute to the quality of service experienced by all service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBlossom EathertonJob titleRecruitment ManagerEmail addresscherry.eatherton@southend.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
